Fun plugin trick, instead of having your openmhz settings mixed in with systems and other top-level trunk-recorder configs, you can also just treat it as any other external plugin and give it it's own block.
```json
"plugins": [
{
  {
  "name": "Openmhz",
  "library": "libopenmhz_uploader.so",
  "enabled": true,
  "uploadServer": "https://api.openmhz.com",
  "systems": [
          {
                  "shortName": "clmrn",
                  "apiKey": "hahayeahnope"
          }
  ]
},
```

